article.headline: Jacksonville 89, FLA Inst Tech 60
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Fla. (AP) -- Evan Jefferson and Tyrone Curnell came off the bench to score career highs of 18 points and lead Jacksonville to an 89-60 win over Florida Tech on Wednesday. Jefferson connected on 7-of-10 shots, including four shots from beyond the arc, while Curnell dropped in 7-of-11 shots and added four free throws. Jefferson hit back-to-back 3-point baskets and added a layup off a fast break in a 62-second span early in the game. It was part of a 19-0 Dolphins (2-2) surge in which they built their lead to 24-6. Curnell topped his season best of 10 points in Jacksonville's previous game against Florida. He also matched teammate Jesse Kimbrough's team high of 8 rebounds. Justin Sedlak led Florida Tech (1-2) with a game-high 21 points. Florida Tech made a run late in the first half to cut the margin to 11 points, but Jacksonville scored eight consecutive points in the final two minutes to take a 46-27 lead at halftime. The Dolphins built their lead to 30 points at 89-59 in the closing minutes of the game. Three other Dolphins finished in double digits: Marcus Allen with 15, Ben Smith with 12 and Kimbrough with 11. Other than Jefferson's shooting from beyond the arc, the Dolphins made just 2-of-13 shots from 3-point range.
